  "texts": [
    "The algorithm saves every transition (consisting of state, action, reward, and next state) in the replay memory.",
    "Random mini-batches of experiences are sampled from the replay memory during training.",
    "This aids in disrupting the temporal relationship between successive experiences and enhances the stability of the learning process.",
    "The Q-network is updated by minimizing the temporal difference error between the predicted Q-values and target Q-values.",
    "The goal values are calculated using the observed rewards and the highest Q-value for the subsequent state."
  ],
